### Tokio: Spawn Blocking Task Using MPSC Channel for Communication

Source: https://docs.rs/tokio/latest/tokio/task/fn.spawn_blocking

Illustrates using `spawn_blocking` in conjunction with Tokio's MPSC (Multi-Producer, Single-Consumer) channel for communication. The blocking task sends data (`blocking_send`) into the channel, while the async task receives it (`recv`). This pattern is effective for offloading work and streaming results from a blocking operation to the async runtime.

```rust
use tokio::task;
use tokio::sync::mpsc;

let (tx, mut rx) = mpsc::channel(2);
let start = 5;
let worker = task::spawn_blocking(move || {
    for x in 0..10 {
        // Stand in for complex computation
        tx.blocking_send(start + x).unwrap();
    }
});

let mut acc = 0;
while let Some(v) = rx.recv().await {
    acc += v;
}
assert_eq!(acc, 95);
worker.await.unwrap();
```

