### Correct Tokio Select! Usage for Timeouts

Source: https://docs.rs/tokio/latest/tokio/macro.select

Provides a corrected version of the previous example, demonstrating the proper way to handle timeouts with Tokio's select! macro. This version avoids the race condition by using a loop and breaking upon timeout.

```rust
use tokio::time::{self, Duration};

async fn some_async_work() {
    // do work
}

let sleep = time::sleep(Duration::from_millis(50));
tokio::pin!(sleep);

loop {
    tokio::select! {
        _ = &mut sleep => {
            println!("operation timed out");
            break;
        }
        _ = some_async_work() => {
            println!("operation completed");
        }
    }
}
```

