### Initialize JSON Formatting Subscriber with Error Handling in Rust

Source: https://docs.rs/tracing-subscriber/latest/src/tracing_subscriber/fmt/mod

Creates a subscriber for JSON output with field flattening, using try_init to handle errors if setting the default fails. Requires fmt and json features; returns Result. Inputs: configuration options; outputs: Ok if successful. Limitations: requires Send+Sync error type.

```rust
use std::error::Error;

fn init_subscriber() -> Result<(), Box<dyn Error + Send + Sync + 'static>> {
    tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        // Configure the subscriber to emit logs in JSON format.
        .json()
        // Configure the subscriber to flatten event fields in the output JSON objects.
        .flatten_event(true)
        // Set the subscriber as the default, returning an error if this fails.
        .try_init()?;

    Ok(())
}
